    "result": {"data":{"strapiPost":{"strapiId":3697,"title":"Permitted to Build","topic":"Development","slug":"permitted-to-build","coverImage":{"publicURL":"/static/ed188a58354fdc54c016bcef069f492a/b2918cdb1d386c86f61f7d8b5df74982.JPG"},"photoCredit":"NWA Daily","date":"2021-10-08","content":"<p>Weâ€™ve seen this week that there is a <a href=\"https://www.northwestarkansasdaily.com/post/a-place-for-everyone\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">need for housing</a> in Northwest Arkansas. Here are some numbers to put it all in context.</p><ul><li><strong>Build:</strong> For the first 8 months of 2021, the 4 largest cities in NWA have had more building permits issued than the same amount of time last year by nearly a third. There have been a collective <a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2021/10/nwa-residential-building-surges-through-august/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">1,337</a> residential building permits issued this year through August.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Value: </strong>The City of Fayetteville was granted the most permits with <a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2021/10/nwa-residential-building-surges-through-august/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">517</a>. Rogers is next with <a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2021/10/nwa-residential-building-surges-through-august/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">367</a>. Bentonville received <a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2021/10/nwa-residential-building-surges-through-august/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">258</a>, and Springdale, <a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2021/10/nwa-residential-building-surges-through-august/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">195</a>. The combined value of permits is over <a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2021/10/nwa-residential-building-surges-through-august/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">$424m</a>, which is up <a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2021/10/nwa-residential-building-su